body:
I can see both pros and cons for re-throwing v.s. logging-as-error, depending on whether users would treat two clients sharing the same client id and hence some of them may not register this information as FATAL or not. I think we did not carefully discuss about this when adding this class originally.

I'd vote for catching-and re-throwing since we are doing this in `JMXReporter` as well, so it seems like we are treating it as a fatal error:

```
private void reregister(KafkaMbean mbean) {
        unregister(mbean);
        try {
            ManagementFactory.getPlatformMBeanServer().registerMBean(mbean, mbean.name());
        } catch (JMException e) {
            throw new KafkaException("Error registering mbean " + mbean.name(), e);
        }
    }
```
